      "timestamp": "2026-04-26T18:00:00Z",
      "error_message": "ImportError: cannot import name 'is_torch_fx_available' from 'transformers.utils.import_utils'",
      "file": "base/DeepSeek-Coder-V2-Lite-Instruct/modeling_deepseek.py",
      "root_cause": "DS-Coder's modeling_deepseek.py was written for transformers 4.x. The symbol `is_torch_fx_available` was removed in transformers 5.x. It is only used to wrap `_prepare_4d_causal_attention_mask` with `torch.fx.wrap` for FX tracing, which we don't use.",
      "fix": "Wrapped the import in try/except ImportError and provided a `def is_torch_fx_available(): return False` fallback. The downstream `if is_torch_fx_available():` block then no-ops.",
      "tags": [
        "transformers-5x",
        "trust_remote_code",
        "deepseek-v2",
        "compat"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [],
      "occurrences": 1,
      "last_seen": "2026-04-26T18:00:00Z",
      "notes": "HF caches a copy of trust_remote_code modules under /srv/dev-disk-by-uuid-.../huggingface/modules/transformers_modules/<MODEL>/. After patching base/, you must `rm -rf` that cache dir or HF will keep loading the old copy and the patch will appear to do nothing."
